- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely because probabilistic automata are used in AI applications, and the paper discusses the belief-state transformer as a way to represent and manipulate probability distributions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility because the paper deals with the semantics of a programming construct (probabilistic automata) and presents a proof technique for verifying their behavior. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility because the paper deals with the algebraic structure of probability distributions and their manipulation. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possibility because the paper deals with automata and their semantics.
